The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 February is 216,492 (24,952 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 February, there were 8,547 new confirmed cases (985.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 February, there were 10,697 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 20% (2,150 fewer cases).
